{65188=BERKELEY, California (Ticker) -- Reggie Robertson threw two 
touchdown passes and Adimchinobe Echemandu rushed for 127 yards
as California rolled to a 34-2 victory over Southern
Mississippi.

One week after throwing three TDs against Kansas State,
Robertson connected with Brandon Hall and Garrett Cross.  He
threw for 257 yards last week and completed 9-of-14 passes for
142 yards in this one as California (1-1) won its home opener.

In their first meeting with Southern Mississippi, the Golden
Bears used terrific special teams and tough defense.  They
blocked a punt for a score three minutes into the second
quarter, registered seven sacks and used an interception by Mike
McGrath to set up Robertson's four-yard TD pass to Hall with 16
seconds left in the first half.

After Cross's 30-yard TD made it 27-2 with 9:53 left in the
third, Echemandu raced in for a 60-yard score to cap the scoring
with 10:20 to play.

Mickey D'Angelo threw for 163 yards for the Golden Eagles, who
were playing their season opener and lost their first game
against a Pac-10 Conference opponent.

D'Angelo completed 16-of-26 passes, but was sacked four times.}
